Feature: Log In to https://greenflag-qa-experience.dev.mycro.app/login
This feature allows a user to login to the green flag qa expereince website.

#Assumptions:
*The user has a valid login credential already registered
*The user has a valid password
*The user is able to open the given link in any given browser

#Scenario: Screen Elements Check
Given the user opens the link "https://greenflag-qa-experience.dev.mycro.app"
When the link successfully opens
Then the user must see a "Username" field, a "Password" field and a "Log In" button below which is in Pink

#Scenario: Credentials Validation
Given the user is on the greenflag qa experience page
When the user inputs a valid username in the "Username" field and 
the user inputs a valid password of 8-16 characters in the "Password" field
Then the "Log In" button becomes enabled for the user to log in.

#Scenario: Charaters entered in the Password field is masked as Asterisk or Bullet characters
Given the user has already entered the Username in the "Username" field
When the user enters Password in the "Password" field
Then the Password is masked as Asterisk or Bullet characters

#Scenario: Invalid Credentials Response
Given the user is on the greenflag qa expereince page
When the user inputs an invalid username in the "Username" field and 
the user inputs an invalid password in the "Password" field
Then the "Log In" button must remain disabled  
and the system must display "Error Message" under both the "Username" and "Password" fields

#Scenario: Blank Fields
Given the user is on the greenflag qa expereince page
When the user enters a valid Username in the "Username" field
and leaves the "Password" field is left blank
Then the "Log In" button must remain disabled 
and "Error message" is displayed under the "Password" field

Given the user is on the greenflag qa expereince page
When the user leaves the "Username" field blank 
and enters a Password in the "Password" field
Then the "Log In" button must remain disabled 
and "Error message" is displayed under the "Username" field

#Scenario: Log In with valid credentials
Given the user inputs "qa@greenflag.com" in the "Username" field
and "Password1" in the "Password" field
and the "Log In" button becomes enabled
When the user clicks on the "Log In" button
Or the user hits the return key
Then the system must sign the user in 
and display the "Successfully logged in" message in a new screen.

#Assumptions:
*The user is already on the greenflag qa experience page

#Scenario: Navigating back to the Login Screen
Given the user has successfully logged in
When the user taps on the back button on the browser
Then the user must be returned to the "Login" screen with the "Username" and "Password" fields cleared


#Scenario: Minimum and Maximum Characters for Password field
Given the user enters a valid username in the "Username" field
When the user inputs a password which is less than 8 characters in the Password field
or the user inputs a password which is more than 16 characters in the Password field

Then the "Log In" button must remain disabled 
and "Error message" is displayed under the "Username" field

#Any email with a valid domain is accepted as a Username
#Any password with 8-16 characters is accepted as a Password

#Scenario: Cross Platform 
Given the user has multiple browsers
When the user enters the link in each of those browsers
Then the link must open in all of those browsers
